@startuml
title 1. Start a New Feature (Simplified)
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor Student as S
participant "GitWizard" as W

S -> W : Option 1
W -> S : "List issues (L) or enter number (N)?"
S -> W : L

W -> S : Display open issues\nwith numbers and labels

S -> W : Pick issue #2\n[BR-02] Edit Community

W -> W : Generate branch name:\nfeature/BR-02-edit-existing-community

W -> S : "Branch: feature/BR-02-...\nProceed? (y/n)"
S -> W : y

W -> W : Switch to main\nPull latest\nCreate branch

W -> S : "Feature branch created!\nGo to your IDE."

note right of S
  Go to IDE, implement
  feature, write tests.
  Come back for option 2.
end note
@enduml
